oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.flex.runtime
Class ModelerDependencies.MdsResourceNames

  oracle.apps.fnd.applcore.flex.runtime.ModelerDependencies.MdsResourceNames
Enclosing class:
ModelerDependencies
public static class ModelerDependencies.MdsResourceNames
extends java.lang.Object

A collection of MDS resource names. An MDS resource name is either a package name such as "/a/b/c/" or a document name such as "/o/a/xyz.xml". A package name always ends with "/". In other words, "/a/b/c/" and "/a/b/c" are different resource names -- the former is a package that represents all documents under "/a/b/c/" while the latter is a document named "c" under "/a/b/".

Checks if a resource is in this collection. A resource is in this collection if the resource name is an exact match of a package name or a document name in this collection, or if the resource is under a package in this collection.

asWildcardPatterns

public java.lang.String[] asWildcardPatterns()
Returns the wildcard patterns for this collection. The patterns may cover documents which are not in this collection. It is ensured that all packages and documents in this collection are covered by the returned patterns. Common patterns such as "/oracle/apps/flex/%" and "/oracle/apps/publicFlex/%" are always included.

Returns:
the wildcard patterns for this collection
